Springer Plans to Combat Apple With IKiosk, Handelsblatt Says

-- B y   C o r n e l i u s   R a h n
-- 
2011-06-28T16:26:08Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-28/springer-plans-to-combat-apple-with-ikiosk-handelsblatt-says.html
Axel Springer AG (SPR)  plans to open its
iKiosk digital sales platform to competing publishers in coming
months to offer alternatives to  Apple Inc. (AAPL) ’s iTunes,
 Handelsblatt  reported, citing Georg Konjovic, the company’s
director of premium content.  The platform will charge less than the 30 percent fee on
iTunes sales, the newspaper cited Konjovic as saying.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Cornelius Rahn in Frankfurt at 
 crahn2@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
 Kenneth Wong  in Berlin at 
 kwong11@bloomberg.net  